		{"id":"n_sakura","type":"text","text":"## SAKURA\n*Study of Astrophysical Key reactions in the Universe with low-energy RI beam Apparatus*\nSurrogate (d,p) reactions for astrophysical cross sections","x":100,"y":0,"width":220,"height":200,"color":"4"},
		{"id":"n_structure","type":"text","text":"## Nuclear Structure\nDeformation coexistence\nCollective motions (rotational, vibrational)\nExtreme rotation & high-spin states","x":-480,"y":200,"width":280,"height":140,"color":"4"},
		{"id":"n_reaction_dynamics","type":"text","text":"## Nuclear Reaction Dynamics\nr-process nucleosynthesis\nSuperheavy element production\nNuclear waste transmutation","x":-480,"y":420,"width":280,"height":140,"color":"4"},
		{"id":"n_nuspeq","type":"text","text":"## NUSPEQ (Aoi Group)\nCollaborating group at CNS\nCAT-M active-target TPC\nShared OEDO-SHARAQ infrastructure","x":-480,"y":640,"width":280,"height":140,"color":"3"},
		{"id":"g_facilities","type":"group","x":1300,"y":-60,"width":920,"height":880,"color":"1","label":"Facilities & Instruments"},
		{"id":"n_oedo","type":"text","text":"## OEDO Decelerator\n*Optimized Energy-Degrading Optics for RI beams*\nAchromatic energy degradation\nOutput: 10-50 MeV/u\nFirst beam: June 2017","x":1340,"y":0,"width":280,"height":160,"color":"1"},
		{"id":"n_sharaq","type":"text","text":"## SHARAQ Spectrometer\nQQDQD magnetic spectrometer\nResolving power: dp/p = 1/15000\nHigh-resolution missing-mass spectroscopy","x":1660,"y":0,"width":280,"height":140,"color":"1"},
		{"id":"n_ribf","type":"text","text":"## RIKEN RIBF / BigRIPS\nProjectile fragmentation & in-flight fission\nSecondary beams at ~200 MeV/u\nUpstream of OEDO-SHARAQ","x":1340,"y":240,"width":280,"height":140,"color":"1"},
		{"id":"n_diamond","type":"text","text":"## Diamond Detectors\nCVD diamond, ultra-thin (<10 um)\nSub-100 ps timing resolution\nBeam tracking & PID at OEDO\nRadiation-hard, room-temperature","x":1660,"y":240,"width":280,"height":160,"color":"1"},
		{"id":"n_thgem","type":"text","text":"## DG-M-THGEM / Active Target TPC\nDual-gain THGEM prototype\nBeam region gain <100, Recoil gain ~2000\nStable to 2.5 x 10^6 pps\n(Iwamoto, Ota, Imai — PTEP 2023)","x":1340,"y":480,"width":340,"height":160,"color":"1"},
		{"id":"g_physics","type":"group","x":100,"y":820,"width":1200,"height":580,"color":"2","label":"Physics Topics"},
		{"id":"n_dgt","type":"text","text":"## Double Gamow-Teller Giant Resonance\nTwo-phonon giant resonance (DZ = +/-2)\nFirst candidate observation in 48Ca\n(Sasano, Yako, Imai — PTEP 2024)","x":140,"y":880,"width":320,"height":140,"color":"2"},
		{"id":"n_dcx","type":"text","text":"## Charge-Exchange Reactions (DCX)\n48Ca(12C, 12Be(0+_2)) at 250 MeV/u\nHeavy-ion double charge-exchange\nDirect mechanism at high energy","x":140,"y":1100,"width":320,"height":140,"color":"2"},
		{"id":"n_surrogate","type":"text","text":"## Surrogate Reactions (d,p)\n79Se(d,p) neutron capture cross-section\nConstrains (n,gamma) on unstable nuclei\nFlagship PLB 2024 paper (Imai first-author)","x":520,"y":880,"width":320,"height":140,"color":"2"},
		{"id":"n_0vbb","type":"text","text":"## 0vbb Connection\nNeutrinoless double-beta decay\nDGT matrix element linearly correlated\nwith 0vbb NME (Shimizu et al. PRL 2018)\nIndependent constraint on NMEs","x":900,"y":880,"width":340,"height":160,"color":"5"},
		{"id":"n_79se","type":"text","text":"## 79Se Neutron Capture (r-process)\nSurrogate measurement for nuclear waste\ntransmutation & r-process nucleosynthesis\nPress coverage: UTokyo, ScienceDaily, Phys.org","x":520,"y":1100,"width":340,"height":140,"color":"2"}
